President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation recognizing Emergency Medical Services (EMS) Week and honoring the contributions and lifesaving actions of EMS providers. The proclamation highlights the dedication, courage, and skill of career and volunteer first responders who provide emergency medical treatment in times of dire need. It also acknowledges the efforts of EMS providers during natural disasters and the opioid crisis, emphasizing the need for training and equipping first responders to safely and effectively respond to crises. The proclamation concludes by urging Americans to show their support for local EMS professionals through various programs and activities.